column7: The mammal collection includes skins, skeletons and mounts of 23 orders. Most specimens are from Arkansas.  Voucher specimens for Sealander and Height (1986) Mammals of Arkansas form the basis for the research collection, with recent additions from the Museum of Discovery in Little Rock. The majority of these specimens are rodents.
